def soft_threshold(rho,lamda):
    if rho < - lamda:
        return (rho + lamda)
    elif rho >  lamda:
        return (rho - lamda)
    else: 
        return 0

def coordinate_descent(beta, X, y, lamda, lamda_record, num_iters):
    m,n = X.shape
    # loop of iteration
    error = []
    error.append(mean_squared_error(y, (X @ beta)))
    for iter in range(num_iters):
        # cycle loop for each components
        for i in range(n):
            X_i = X[:,i].reshape(-1,1)
            y_pred = X @ beta
            s_i = X_i.T @ (y - y_pred  + beta[i]*X_i)
            beta[i] =  soft_threshold(s_i, lamda)

        if lamda_record:
            error.append(mean_squared_error(y, (X @ beta)))
    
    return beta.flatten(), error

X, y  = datasets.make_regression(n_samples=100, n_features=10)
# data normalization
X = X / (np.linalg.norm(X,axis = 0))
y  = y.reshape(-1,1)
In [13]:
# Initialize variables
m,n = X.shape
initial_beta = np.ones((n,1))
beta_list = []
lamda = np.logspace(0,4,300)/10 #Range of lambda values
lamda = np.append(0, lamda)
num_iters = 100

Test_score = []
lamda_record = [0,100,200]
Error = []
for i, l in enumerate(lamda):
    initial_beta = np.ones((n,1))
    if i in lamda_record:
        print("error record at ", i)
        beta, error = coordinate_descent(initial_beta, X, y, lamda = l, lamda_record = True, num_iters=num_iters)    
        Error.append(error)
    else:
        beta, _ = coordinate_descent(initial_beta, X, y, lamda = l, lamda_record = False, num_iters=num_iters)    

    Test_score.append(mean_squared_error(y, (X @ beta)))
    beta_list.append(beta)
beta_lasso = np.stack(beta_list).T

Alpha = lamda[lamda_record]
Error_SGD= []
for alpha in Alpha:
    initial_w = np.ones((n,1))
    error_sgd = []
    sgd_reg = SGDRegressor(loss='squared_error', alpha=alpha, max_iter=1, tol=1e-6, penalty='l1')
    sgd_reg.fit(X,y,coef_init=initial_w)
    y_pred = sgd_reg.predict(X)
    error_sgd.append(mean_squared_error(y, y_pred))
    for epoch in range(num_iters):
        sgd_reg.partial_fit(X, y.ravel())
        y_pred = sgd_reg.predict(X)
        error_sgd.append(mean_squared_error(y, y_pred))
    Error_SGD.append(error_sgd)

n,_ = beta_lasso.shape
plt.figure(figsize = (18,4))
plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
for i in range(n):
    plt.plot(lamda, beta_lasso[i], label = '$\\beta${}'.format(i))
plt.xscale('log')
plt.xlabel('$\\lambda$')
plt.ylabel('Regression Coefficients ($\\beta$)')
plt.title('Synthetic Random Regression Dataset')
plt.legend()
plt.axis('tight')

plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
plt.xscale('log')
plt.xlabel('$\\lambda$')
plt.plot(lamda, Test_score)
plt.xlabel('$\\lambda$')
plt.ylabel('Regression Deviance')
plt.title('Regression Deviance of Different ($\\lambda$s)')
plt.axis('tight')

plt.subplot(1, 3, 3)
for j, error_i in enumerate(Error):
    plt.plot([i for i in range(len(error_i))], error_i, label = '$CD-\\lambda$={:.3f}'.format(lamda[lamda_record[j]]))
for j, error_i in enumerate(Error_SGD):
    plt.plot([i for i in range(len(error_i))], error_i, label = '$SGD-\\lambda$={:.3f}'.format(lamda[lamda_record[j]]))
plt.xlabel('iter')
plt.ylabel('Regression Deviance')
plt.title('Regression Deviance')
plt.axis('tight')
plt.legend()
plt.savefig('/home/cao.1378/courses/ECE6500/Random.png', bbox_inches='tight')

# Initialize variables

beta_list = list()

for i, l in enumerate(lamda):
    initial_beta = np.ones((n,1))
    if i in lamda_record:
        print("error record at ", i)
        beta, error = coordinate_descent(initial_beta, X, y, lamda = l, lamda_record = True, num_iters=num_iters)    
        Error.append(error)
    else:
        beta, _ = coordinate_descent(initial_beta, X, y, lamda = l, lamda_record = False, num_iters=num_iters)    

    Test_score.append(mean_squared_error(y, (X @ beta)))
    beta_list.append(beta)
beta_lasso = np.stack(beta_list).T


Alpha = lamda[lamda_record]
Error_SGD= []
for alpha in Alpha:
    initial_w = np.ones((n,1))
    error_sgd = []
    sgd_reg = SGDRegressor(loss='squared_error', alpha=alpha, max_iter=1, tol=1e-6, penalty='l1')
    sgd_reg.fit(X,y,coef_init=initial_w)
    y_pred = sgd_reg.predict(X)
    error_sgd.append(mean_squared_error(y, y_pred))

        sgd_reg.partial_fit(X, y.ravel())
        y_pred = sgd_reg.predict(X)
        error_sgd.append(mean_squared_error(y, y_pred))
    Error_SGD.append(error_sgd)
